article_title: Jackson County needs more space to serve OHP clients
article_text: Sign up for our newsletter and have the top headlines from your community delivered right to your inbox.

article_metadata.description: In order to serve a burgeoning number of Oregon Health Plan patients, Jackson County will keep and remodel buildings it had planned to sell.The county is seeking bids on a project to remodel three buildings located between 1000 and 1025 E. Main St. in downtown Medford.County employees working in veterans' services, environmental health and other areas now work in the buildings, but officials had hoped to move them into the new Jackson County Health & Human Services building at 140 S. Holly
article_metadata.author: Vickie Aldous Mail Tribune
